   <RulesElement name="Sneak Attack" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_322" source="Player&apos;s Handbook" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:47:04 PM" >
      <Category> 1 </Category>
      <Flavor> As a rogue, you fight fair only when you have no other choice. You are at your best when you have the advantage over an enemy, such as when you and an ally attack the foe from opposite sides or you deliver a surprise assault. </Flavor>
      <specific name="Short Description"> Once per turn, if you have combat advantage and hit with a crossbow, light blade,shortbow, or sling, deal extra damage. </specific>
      <specific name="Level"> 1 </specific>
      <specific name="Usage"> turn </specific>
      <rules>
         <statadd name="Sneak Attack Dice" value="+2" />
         <statadd name="Sneak Attack Dice" value="+1" requires="Paragon Tier" />
         <statadd name="Sneak Attack Dice" value="+2" requires="Epic Tier" />
		 <textstring name="implement:damage" value="+Sneak Attack damage" condition="once per turn (Sneak Attack)" />
         <modify name="this" Field="Usage" value="turn" />
      </rules>
When you make an attack with a light blade, a hand crossbow, a shortbow, or a sling and hit an enemy granting combat advantage to you, that enemy takes extra damage based on your level (see the Sneak Attack table). You can deal this extra damage only once per turn.

SNEAK ATTACK
&lt;table&gt;Level	Extra Damage
1-10	2d6
11-20	3d6
21-30	5d6&lt;/table&gt;
   </RulesElement>
   
