   <RulesElement name="Protector Spirit" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_1251" source="Player&apos;s Handbook 2" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:47:04 PM" >
      <Category> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_855,1 </Category>
      <specific name="Short Description"> Ally adjacent to spirit companion gains hit points equal to your Con mod with second wind or your healing power </specific>
      <specific name="Level"> 1 </specific>
      <specific name="Powers"> ID_FMP_POWER_5389,ID_FMP_POWER_6521 </specific>
      <specific name="type"> At-Will </specific>
      <specific name="Class"> ID_FMP_CLASS_147 </specific>
      <specific name="_DisplayPowers"> ID_FMP_POWER_5389,ID_FMP_POWER_6521 </specific>
      <rules>
         <statadd name="AC" value="+Constitution modifier" type="Ability" not-wearing="armor:heavy" />
         <grant name="ID_FMP_POWER_5389" type="Power" />
         <grant name="ID_FMP_POWER_6521" type="Power" />
      </rules>
You draw on the strength of the bear or a similar protective spirit to defend and bolster your allies.
Spirit Boon: Any ally adjacent to your spirit companion regains additional hit points equal to your Constitution modifier when he or she uses second wind or when you use a healing power on him or her.
In addition, while you are not wearing heavy armor, you can use your Constitution modifier in place of your Dexterity or Intelligence modifier to determine your AC.
Spirit&apos;s Shield: You gain the spirit&apos;s shield power, an attack you make through your spirit companion as an opportunity action.
At-Will Attack Power: You gain the protecting strike power. You choose a second at-will attack power as normal.
   </RulesElement>
   
   <RulesElement name="World Speaker Spirit" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_2004" source="Primal Power" revision-date="10/5/2010 1:47:05 PM" >
      <Category> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_855,1 </Category>
      <specific name="Short Description" />
